cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about conversational machine comprehension, which involves natural language processing and understanding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a new mechanism for explicitly modeling information gain, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also achieves state-of-the-art performance, which involves optimization and learning, making cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category. The proposed model also involves neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a conversational QA dataset and a sequential instruction understanding dataset, which involves computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
